question: Erosion and weathering can both cause changes to the surface of Earth. Which of the following happens only because of erosion and NOT because of weathering?
candidate_answers: (A) Rocks form deep underground. (B) Rocks become smooth and round. (C) Rocks are broken apart into small pieces. (D) Rocks are moved from one place to another.
answer: Rocks are broken apart into small pieces.
label: C
